wiki.summary: “SUMMER RENAISSANCE” is the closing track on Beyoncé’s seventh studio album, RENAISSANCE, sampling “I Feel Love” by Donna Summer. The track title itself is a tribute to the Queen of Disco using her stage name “SUMMER,” followed by “RENAISSANCE,” which means “re-birth” in French. Beyoncé states in the last track of the album that the message being portrayed is a celebration, rebirth & innovation of past sounds (such as disco, house, vogue & ballroom) founded by artists such as Donna Summer. Read more on Last.fm.
